She's more special than you, Bong.

64
00:06:08,791 --> 00:06:10,250
Do your eyes hurt?

65
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,958
Take these.

66
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,833
We'll get it signed next Monday.

67
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,291
<i>This is our headteacher.</i>

68
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:34,000
<i>She looks cold but has a big heart.</i>

69
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,125
So weird. Like a freak!

70
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,208
Looks so weird.

71
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:59,125
- So ugly! Hideous!
- Which planet is she from?

72
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:02,458
This is the last time I warn you.

73
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:05,291
You care about everything but your study.

74
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:07,958
Going to international school
isn't doing anything you want.

75
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:09,083
In my class,

76
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:11,791
anyone who can't study well
must repeat a grade.

77
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,166
Don't ever blame me!

78
00:07:13,916 --> 00:07:16,291
An! Introduce yourself!

79
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:23,875
Gosh! Hurry up,
new friend. We have to study.

80
00:07:23,958 --> 00:07:26,916
Hurry up! Come on!

81
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:32,041
I'm An.

82
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:33,583
Oh my!

83
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:35,375
Why does it take her so long?

84
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:38,083
Such a role model!

85
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,791
You're wearing uniform to the extra class.

86
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:43,583
Come on, guys! Don't tease her.

87
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:45,666
Wow!

88
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:48,791
I used to go to public school.

89
00:07:49,291 --> 00:07:53,458
My Dad said I would be
more confident in this school.

90
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:58,458
There's a question you haven't answered.

91
00:07:58,541 --> 00:07:59,666
What's your hobby?

92
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:01,416
I love reading books.

93
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,791
Wow! Tell us
some interesting stories.

94
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,791
I read about
the butterfly effect, the chaos theory,

95
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:08,416
the perfection of wisdom,

96
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:11,166
Greek mythology, Ancient Rome.

97
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:13,000
Do you love doing anything else?

98
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:16,208
Something less weird, like
playing instruments, singing, bowling.

99
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:18,333
Boring.

100
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,041
An, you can sit over there.

101
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,875
- Wow!
- How lucky she is!

102
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:32,875
- Hi!
- Is it all okay?

103
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:41,500
Sit next to Quan.

104
00:08:43,291 --> 00:08:46,458
<i>So great to sit near a handsome
guy, although being teased a lot.</i>

105
00:08:46,541 --> 00:08:48,583
<i>How lucky I am!</i>

106
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:55,083
Why does your hair
have a lot of split ends?

107
00:09:00,875 --> 00:09:02,375
Why are you as fit as a bodybuilder?

108
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,708
Why didn't you eat anything?

109
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:12,250
What's wrong?

110
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:15,291
You didn't even touch
the peanut butter made by your Dad.

111
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:17,541
Why did you use
the whole bottle of medicated oil?

112
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,041
I'm fine, Nanny!

113
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:35,125
Your Dad dropped by your school,
then he rushed to the airport.

114
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:48,875
Apply for Miss Idol?

115
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:50,250
Yup!

116
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:52,625
You're a potential contestant.

117
00:09:52,708 --> 00:09:54,833
Join our club and be
our entrant for the contest.

118
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:56,291
I…

119
00:09:56,375 --> 00:09:57,291
- I…
- Don't worry!

120
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,708
Join our club,
okay? This world will be yours.

121
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:10,291
There are books on economics,
politics, philosophy, and critical theory.

122
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:13,083
Over here are books on
religions, spirit, theology, literature.

123
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:15,916
There are also books on applied science.

124
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,416
On economics there is

125
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,476
<i>"The Prize: The Epic Quest for Oil,
Money &amp; Power"</i> by Daniel Yergin.

126
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:24,500
On psychology there's <i>"The</i>
<i>first and last freedom"</i> by Krishnamurti.

127
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,708
Or <i>"The power of Now"</i> by Eckhart Tolle.

128
00:10:26,791 --> 00:10:27,833
On political philosophy,

129
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:31,041
<i>"The social contract"</i> by Jean
Jacques Rousseau is also a good one.

130
00:10:31,125 --> 00:10:32,541
You can visit the Tam bookstore

131
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:35,250
on Nguyen Thi Minh Khai St.
Take a right to 496 Alley.

132
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:39,041
Then turn to 20th
Street. From there, turn to 20/10/7.

133
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:40,166
Many good, cheap books.

134
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:47,958
I gotta go home. Please find someone else.

135
00:10:57,500 --> 00:11:00,083
I'm sorry! Are you okay?

136
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:24,833
<i>It seems this
is the book my Dad told me about before.</i>

137
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:31,250
<i>You've just heard the song "Our Memory"</i>

138
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:32,916
<i>on</i> "Tell Us Your Story on Friday".

139
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,375
<i>From our listener,
Hoai Thuong to her friend, Cong Danh.</i>

140
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,333
<i>May your friendship never die.</i>

141
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:40,750
<i>Up next is the song "Waiting
for you" from Ms. Lien to Mr. Tho.</i>

142
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:45,666
<i>Her message says "I've
been looking for you as long as I can.</i>

143
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:47,041
<i>If you get this message,</i>

144
00:12:47,125 --> 00:12:52,750
<i>please contact me via
my number 0937005123</i>

145
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,250
<i>Miss you forever."</i>

146
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:58,208
Here you are.

147
00:13:23,125 --> 00:13:24,916
Poor you!

148
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:26,916
Come here with us!

149
00:13:27,583 --> 00:13:28,791
Sit down!

150
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:33,375
Here are some Fresh
cookies. So yummy! Try it!

151
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,541
<i>Jeez! I'm trapped.</i>

152
00:13:48,583 --> 00:13:50,416
<i>Why was I so stupid that time?</i>

153
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:53,375
What have you done, Duong?

154
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:54,833
I am starving.

155
00:13:54,916 --> 00:13:56,583
An! An!

156
00:14:13,416 --> 00:14:16,791
An! Hold this please.
I'll go get something to clean the table.

157
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:18,500
Who's that?

158
00:14:18,583 --> 00:14:19,875
Who's up there?

159
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,125
Watch out!

160
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,916
That fat girl is so savage.

161
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:32,833
Gosh! What's wrong, An?

162
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:34,041
Come here! Let me help.

163
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:36,625
Any tissue?

164
00:14:42,666 --> 00:14:44,583
Oops! It's soaking wet.

165
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:46,541
You should buy a new one.

166
00:14:50,125 --> 00:14:53,750
It's my Dad's
present from his business trip.

167
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,083
It isn't available here.

168
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:39,458
Daddy's home!

169
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:42,267
Something seems wrong with you.

170
00:16:42,291 --> 00:16:44,625
I had to cancel the Singapore
meeting tomorrow morning.

171
00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:47,541
I'm fine, Dad. Have you had dinner yet?

172
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:49,025
Did you remember your stomach meds?

173
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:58,413
Do you like the new school?

174
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:22,291
No man is an island.

175
00:17:23,416 --> 00:17:25,166
Even books need to rely on one another.

176
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:27,250
Don't isolate yourself, my dear.

177
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:49,375
Hey.

178
00:17:49,458 --> 00:17:50,666
What's that?

179
00:17:57,666 --> 00:17:59,291
My cousin also has a book like yours.

180
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:27,875
Here's your stomach medicine, Dad.

181
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,458
- Thanks.
- I'm off for school, Dad.

182
00:19:30,541 --> 00:19:32,625
Remember to make more friends, dear.

183
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:41,375
Do you still want to
go to Harvard University?

184
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:45,750
I've told you. Your GPA is not
all you need to get into Harvard.

185
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:47,750
GPA is just a part of it.

186
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:51,291
They're looking for active students.

187
00:19:51,958 --> 00:19:54,478
If your profile has lots of great
extra-curricular achievements,

188
00:19:54,666 --> 00:19:56,250
you'll have more chance to get in.

189
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:59,208
Does taking part in Miss Idol count, Dad?

190
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:00,916
Of course!

191
00:20:02,875 --> 00:20:07,083
As the club president,
on the day An joins our club,

192
00:20:07,166 --> 00:20:10,125
I'd like to ask for
your blessing, Mr. Einstein.

193
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:13,083
Please bless her

194
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:15,583
so that she can
contribute to human development

195
00:20:15,666 --> 00:20:17,458
with her knowledge and intelligence.

196
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:20,833
Namo Amitabha!

197
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:26,541
I'm sorry. Thank you, Mr. Einstein.

198
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:37,208
Alright! Let's smell 100 books here

199
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:39,500
to absorb Mr. Einstein's philosophy, An.

200
00:20:43,416 --> 00:20:44,916
There are four rounds in total.

201
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,291
Round One, Facebook photo.

202
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:47,916
Round Two, Knowledge.

203
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,250
Round Three, Interview.

204
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:50,416
And Round Four, Talent.

205
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:55,041
We first need to choose
an impressive outfit for the first round.

206
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:58,833
Please don't.

207
00:21:30,083 --> 00:21:31,583
Give me back my shirt.

208
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,101
<i>The game's just
starting but this shirt's dirty.</i>

209
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:35,125
Okay.

210
00:21:35,166 --> 00:21:37,333
If you take this
I'll take that one home to wash.

211
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:40,625
Then you keep it again? Come on. Hurry up!

212
00:21:42,791 --> 00:21:46,333
Wait a minute! I'll find
Quan to recharge my energy.

213
00:22:00,625 --> 00:22:02,166
Hi, Mom, it's me.

214
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:03,708
What's wrong?

215
00:22:03,791 --> 00:22:05,375
How can I help you?

216
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:09,375
I'm busy, mom.

217
00:22:25,916 --> 00:22:26,916
Thanks.

218
00:22:41,875 --> 00:22:42,875
Ouch!

219
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:51,458
I explained to Quan. Don't worry.

220
00:23:51,541 --> 00:23:54,041
He wouldn't believe
you threw his shirt away.

221
00:24:03,916 --> 00:24:05,458
Look!

222
00:24:05,541 --> 00:24:06,791
- What?
- What's that?

223
00:24:06,875 --> 00:24:08,250
What? Oh my God!

224
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:09,166
Oh my God!

225
00:24:09,250 --> 00:24:10,583
Oh dear! Unbelievable!

226
00:24:10,666 --> 00:24:12,083
Can you see it? Can you see it?

227
00:24:12,166 --> 00:24:13,208
I see all white.

228
00:24:13,291 --> 00:24:14,791
Yeah,

229
00:24:14,875 --> 00:24:15,934
two girls in white dresses.

230
00:24:15,958 --> 00:24:16,791
As white as snow.

231
00:24:16,875 --> 00:24:18,583
No. I mean I see a white wall.

232
00:24:18,666 --> 00:24:20,375
Oops, my bad.

233
00:24:24,416 --> 00:24:28,208
They always make
it exaggerated just to take a photo.

234
00:24:33,458 --> 00:24:36,708
I think we should make
an outfit from recycle bottles

235
00:24:36,791 --> 00:24:39,625
to deliver the message
of environmental protection.

236
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:45,125
And we'll use whatever is available for
makeup. We definitely get tons of likes.

237
00:25:07,375 --> 00:25:09,833
It's strange,

238
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:13,833
but not beautiful, guys.

239
00:25:37,208 --> 00:25:38,541
An has an oval face,

240
00:25:39,416 --> 00:25:40,816
don't do her eyebrows too straight.

241
00:26:04,708 --> 00:26:05,750
See?

242
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:08,041
I told you to let me
make you look prettier

243
00:26:08,125 --> 00:26:09,958
but you didn't want to.

244
00:26:11,125 --> 00:26:12,458
Let's come to the photo shoot.

245
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:23,041
- How beautiful!
- How beautiful!

246
00:26:38,666 --> 00:26:41,625
<i>You need to have more than
500 likes to pass the first round!</i>

247
00:26:48,375 --> 00:26:50,125
She got hundreds of likes.

248
00:26:50,208 --> 00:26:51,583
Prettier than my girlfriend.

249
00:26:51,666 --> 00:26:54,500
<i>We need 100 more likes.</i>

250
00:26:54,583 --> 00:26:56,083
<i>What should we do?</i>

251
00:26:56,166 --> 00:26:58,250
Mother Nature will
bring you natural beauty.

252
00:26:58,333 --> 00:27:01,583
Come and check out
our make-over tips!

253
00:27:01,666 --> 00:27:05,250
And that transformation
happens thanks to cucumbers, tomatoes

254
00:27:05,333 --> 00:27:10,208
eggs, honey, pure water
