you to pay them a visit.

539
00:56:26,541 --> 00:56:28,083
And they've chosen you some ladies.

540
00:56:28,166 --> 00:56:29,958
They wanted to set dates up for you there.

541
00:56:32,666 --> 00:56:36,083
Time really flies. I've been
living in Vietnam for 20 years.

542
00:56:36,583 --> 00:56:39,041
Get yourself ready
for a shower of presents.

543
00:56:39,125 --> 00:56:43,791
On your birthdays,
whether you are home or not,

544
00:56:43,875 --> 00:56:47,458
An always makes you a birthday present.

545
00:56:48,291 --> 00:56:52,041
But you always travel around.
You didn't spend much time with her.

546
00:56:54,416 --> 00:56:55,583
Well…

547
00:56:56,083 --> 00:56:59,875
I'm busy running my business.
I just want her to have a better life.

548
00:57:04,750 --> 00:57:07,500
You think money can
solve all kinds of problems?

549
00:57:08,500 --> 00:57:10,750
What she needs is the love of her dad.

550
00:57:11,250 --> 00:57:13,041
She wants you to spend more time with her.

551
00:57:13,125 --> 00:57:14,625
To be honest,

552
00:57:15,125 --> 00:57:17,958
I think An even loves
you more than her own dad.

553
00:57:18,458 --> 00:57:19,750
But you're always busy.

554
00:57:20,500 --> 00:57:23,000
You don't have
time for her. Poor little girl!

555
00:58:11,041 --> 00:58:13,791
An must have
a really big surprise for you.

556
00:58:51,166 --> 00:58:55,125
<i>Dad, with this lunch
box, you will never be hungry.</i>

557
00:59:05,166 --> 00:59:08,791
<i>Thank you dad, for bringing me
up since I was an abandoned baby.</i>

558
00:59:17,416 --> 00:59:20,791
<i>Dad, hurry up! Let's find
someone to take care of you.</i>

559
00:59:20,875 --> 00:59:24,250
<i>No matter who you get married to, I'll
love that person as much as I love you.</i>

560
00:59:34,166 --> 00:59:37,500
<i>Dad, I present you with a lot of time
so that you can be home with me.</i>

561
00:59:37,583 --> 00:59:44,041
<i>Dad, promise me you'll spend
the whole weekend with me on my birthday.</i>

562
00:59:54,458 --> 00:59:57,458
Hey! Let's go to
the cafeteria to welcome Nhu back!

563
00:59:57,541 --> 00:59:58,541
Yeah!

564
00:59:58,625 --> 00:59:59,916
Hurry up! An's waiting for us.

565
01:00:00,500 --> 01:00:02,875
Forget it. If she's there, we won't go.

566
01:00:07,416 --> 01:00:09,708
What's wrong? I thought you guys…

567
01:00:12,083 --> 01:00:14,666
Thanks to An, Nhu can
recover quickly. We must invite her.

568
01:00:18,416 --> 01:00:21,041
Thanks to An?

569
01:00:23,208 --> 01:00:24,541
You're crazy.

570
01:00:25,333 --> 01:00:27,666
You thought
her heels got broken by chance?

571
01:00:29,208 --> 01:00:35,583
An broke her heels so that Nhu had
an accident and she could replace Nhu.

572
01:00:47,500 --> 01:00:51,625
Quan. I just wanted to harm Ja Ja Bong.

573
01:00:52,583 --> 01:00:54,125
Doesn't matter who you want to harm.

574
01:00:54,916 --> 01:00:56,375
I trusted you.

575
01:00:58,375 --> 01:00:59,375
Quan!

576
01:00:59,875 --> 01:01:01,416
Quan!

577
01:01:04,125 --> 01:01:06,458
Quan, please listen to me!

578
01:01:20,208 --> 01:01:22,208
<i>This is called "Karma".</i>

579
01:01:30,583 --> 01:01:32,000
<i>Joking with me?</i>

580
01:01:32,083 --> 01:01:35,000
<i>You think I don't
know what you're doing behind me?</i>

581
01:02:05,416 --> 01:02:07,375
I can't be seen like this.

582
01:02:07,875 --> 01:02:09,291
The final round is about to come.

583
01:02:10,041 --> 01:02:11,333
And Quan?

584
01:02:13,916 --> 01:02:14,916
Hey!

585
01:02:18,041 --> 01:02:20,083
Time for class. Why are
you still reading books?

586
01:02:44,208 --> 01:02:47,625
- Hello!
- Hello, I'm Khanh An's headteacher.

587
01:02:48,125 --> 01:02:50,000
An missed a crucial test today.

588
01:02:51,958 --> 01:02:55,125
She didn't attend
the class either. Is she okay?

589
01:02:57,041 --> 01:02:59,041
She's fine.

590
01:03:00,166 --> 01:03:03,333
Thank you. I'll talk to her.

591
01:04:21,541 --> 01:04:23,208
Dad, your hair butter is the best.

592
01:04:23,291 --> 01:04:24,916
My hair feels so smooth.

593
01:04:27,375 --> 01:04:28,416
Dad!

594
01:04:34,166 --> 01:04:35,791
Do you want to tell me something?

595
01:04:40,125 --> 01:04:41,500
Did you do anything wrong?

596
01:04:42,708 --> 01:04:44,291
Tell me, An.

597
01:04:45,125 --> 01:04:46,458
I didn't do anything.

598
01:04:46,541 --> 01:04:48,250
I don't know what you're talking about.

599
01:04:59,416 --> 01:05:03,125
Don't you want me to be
more active and beautiful?

600
01:05:03,208 --> 01:05:06,375
I just did what they did.
If they can cheat, then so can I.

601
01:05:06,458 --> 01:05:07,833
Shut up!

602
01:05:11,625 --> 01:05:13,291
The world would be full of bad people

603
01:05:14,458 --> 01:05:15,916
if they all thought like you do.

604
01:05:16,541 --> 01:05:18,125
You think you've become lovely, okay?

605
01:05:18,916 --> 01:05:20,000
In fact,

606
01:05:21,375 --> 01:05:23,500
you just turned out to be a bad one.

607
01:05:34,291 --> 01:05:36,833
I didn't know how to raise you.

608
01:05:40,541 --> 01:05:42,083
This is all my fault.

609
01:05:44,458 --> 01:05:46,166
I'm not capable of being your father.

610
01:05:46,250 --> 01:05:50,583
Dad, I'm wrong. It's my fault. I'm sorry!

611
01:05:51,708 --> 01:05:54,208
Dad! Dad!

612
01:05:54,291 --> 01:05:57,375
Dad! Dad! Dad! Dad!

613
01:05:57,458 --> 01:05:59,166
Dad, don't go.

614
01:05:59,250 --> 01:06:01,250
Dad! Dad!

615
01:06:01,333 --> 01:06:02,416
Dad!

616
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:07,041
Dad, don't leave me, Dad…

617
01:06:07,125 --> 01:06:09,458
Dad!

618
01:06:14,250 --> 01:06:17,500
Dad!

619
01:06:17,583 --> 01:06:21,333
How can my
sweetheart manage to do everything?

620
01:06:21,416 --> 01:06:23,708
There are only two options.

621
01:06:24,708 --> 01:06:27,458
<i>One is to face the pain with discipline.</i>

622
01:06:29,250 --> 01:06:32,166
<i>The other is to confront it with regret.</i>

623
01:06:49,916 --> 01:06:50,916
<i>An is still young,</i>

624
01:06:52,541 --> 01:06:54,041
<i>she won't be able to understand.</i>

625
01:09:39,708 --> 01:09:41,916
Beauty takes…

626
01:09:42,000 --> 01:09:44,708
Takes what? Say it out loud!

627
01:09:44,791 --> 01:09:47,708
Why do you have to mumble?

628
01:09:48,208 --> 01:09:49,583
Beauty takes…

629
01:09:49,666 --> 01:09:50,875
Hold on!

630
01:09:52,041 --> 01:09:53,041
What is that?

631
01:09:56,875 --> 01:09:59,375
The contest hasn't ended
yet. We don't know the winner.

632
01:09:59,458 --> 01:10:02,875
They said they had quit.

633
01:10:04,708 --> 01:10:07,375
The one who signs this form
will be responsible for the contest.

634
01:10:10,166 --> 01:10:12,416
- Does the contest keep going?
- Do they quit?

635
01:10:25,291 --> 01:10:28,000
Hide yourself! Quickly!

636
01:10:53,541 --> 01:10:54,708
I KNOW YOU WON'T LEAVE ME…

637
01:10:54,791 --> 01:10:55,958
LOTS OF MOSQUITOES HERE.

638
01:10:56,041 --> 01:10:58,641
YOU AND NANNY SHOULD TAKE CARE
OF YOURSELF… I'M REALLY SORRY, DAD.

639
01:12:44,416 --> 01:12:47,166
<i>They said, if they forgive each other,</i>

640
01:12:47,250 --> 01:12:50,208
<i>tie a yellow ribbon round the tree.</i>

641
01:13:08,416 --> 01:13:11,208
Thank you, Anh Khue, for
your magnificent performance.

642
01:13:15,125 --> 01:13:19,583
Coming on stage is our candidate
with the most likes and votes.

643
01:13:20,333 --> 01:13:23,208
Please welcome Ja Ja Bong!

644
01:14:32,791 --> 01:14:34,625
Let's welcome
our last performance tonight.

645
01:14:34,708 --> 01:14:36,750
Please give it up for Khanh An!

646
01:14:47,250 --> 01:14:49,208
Woooh look… It's Khanh An.

647
01:15:01,375 --> 01:15:06,875
<i>Time flies quickly, leaving only memories</i>

648
01:15:06,958 --> 01:15:09,041
<i>Dear memories</i>

649
01:15:09,125 --> 01:15:11,916
<i>I will always remember
The voices of my teachers</i>

650
01:15:12,625 --> 01:15:14,875
<i>Dear friends</i>

651
01:15:14,958 --> 01:15:17,625
<i>I will always remember
Those times we argued</i>

652
01:15:18,208 --> 01:15:24,083
<i>So that when we are apart
The longings remain in our hearts</i>

653
01:15:24,166 --> 01:15:29,791
<i>The longings for old friends
And old school</i>

654
01:15:32,291 --> 01:15:34,416
<i>Putting my hand on my lips</i>

655
01:15:34,500 --> 01:15:36,041
<i>To hold back the…</i>

656
01:15:36,125 --> 01:15:38,166
- What happened?
- Oh my God! What happened?

657
01:15:38,250 --> 01:15:40,041
- What's going on?
- The music is off.

658
01:15:40,125 --> 01:15:41,875
- What's going on?
- What happened?

659
01:15:41,958 --> 01:15:44,458
<i>Putting my hand on my lips…</i>

660
01:15:46,791 --> 01:15:52,500
<i>Putting my hand on my lips
To hold back the tears</i>

661
01:15:52,583 --> 01:15:54,250
<i>Time flies so quickly…</i>

662
01:15:54,333 --> 01:15:57,083
- Lip sing?
- Get down!

663
01:15:57,166 --> 01:15:59,208
You're lip-syncing!

664
01:15:59,291 --> 01:16:03,208
- You're lip-syncing!
- Get down! Get down!

665
01:16:04,583 --> 01:16:08,250
- Stop singing.
- Get down! Get down!

666
01:16:17,833 --> 01:16:19,708
How handsome!

667
01:16:19,791 --> 01:16:22,625
What's that? Who's that?

668
01:16:25,083 --> 01:16:26,666
A new performance?

669
01:16:30,458 --> 01:16:34,666
Yes! An has tried a lot to change.

670
01:16:41,166 --> 01:16:44,125
<i>I knew Ja Bong would do
some tricks with the sound system.</i>

671
01:16:44,625 --> 01:16:47,458
<i>Let's turn the tables on her.</i>

672
01:17:12,041 --> 01:17:16,208
<i>Time flies so quickly
Leaving only memories</i>

673
01:17:16,833 --> 01:17:18,833
<i>Dear memories</i>

674
01:17:18,916 --> 01:17:21,541
<i>I will always remember
The voices of my teachers</i>

675
01:17:21,625 --> 01:17:23,541
<i>Dear friends</i>

676
01:17:23,625 --> 01:17:26,166
<i>I will always remember
Those times we argued</i>

677
01:17:26,250 --> 01:17:30,833
<i>So that when we part ways
The longings remain in our hearts</i>

678
01:17:30,916 --> 01:17:34,916
<i>The longings for old friends
And old school</i>

679
01:17:40,541 --> 01:17:44,791
<i>Putting my hand on my lips
To hold back the tears</i>

680
01:17:45,583 --> 01:17:49,583
<i>Could we stop the flying time?</i>

681
01:17:50,250 --> 01:17:54,458
<i>My heart still regrets the good old days</i>

682
01:17:54,541 --> 01:17:55,458
<i>Dear friends</i>

683
01:17:55,541 --> 01:18:00,333
<i>I can still hear your voices
And laughters echoing somewhere</i>

684
01:18:00,416 --> 01:18:06,916
<i>All of my longings
Who can I send them to now?</i>

685
01:18:09,583 --> 01:18:13,583
<i>If you have a wish for this life</i>

686
01:18:14,375 --> 01:18:18,791
<i>Remember to wish for time to retrace</i>

687
01:18:18,875 --> 01:18:23,250
<i>So that the passions and burning desires</i>

688
01:18:23,333 --> 01:18:28,041
<i>Can stay eternal in our hearts</i>

689
01:18:28,125 --> 01:18:33,375
<i>And so that our love
And dreams will never fade</i>

690
01:18:33,458 --> 01:18:37,666
<i>If you have a wish for this life</i>

691
01:18:38,166 --> 01:18:42,583
<i>Remember to wish for time to retrace</i>

692
01:18:42,666 --> 01:18:47,083
<i>So that we can be together again
Making more memories</i>

693
01:18:47,166 --> 01:18:53,000
<i>So that the smiles can stay forever
In our eyes, on our lips</i>

694
01:18:53,083 --> 01:18:58,708
<i>And in our beautiful memories</i>

695
01:19:15,208 --> 01:19:18,541
Dad, why are you here? I thought
you had a business trip today, right?

696
01:19:19,958 --> 01:19:22,083
I have sold all
the stock of the overseas branch.

697
01:19:26,916 --> 01:19:30,291
Miss Idol, An! Miss Idol, An!

698
01:19:30,375 --> 01:19:36,625
Miss Idol, An! Miss Idol, An!

699
01:19:36,708 --> 01:19:40,166
Thanks a lot for trusting
me, my dear teachers and friends.

700
01:19:42,000 --> 01:19:44,000
But I don't think I deserve it.

701
01:19:45,208 --> 01:19:46,500
I'm so sorry.

702
01:19:50,750 --> 01:19:55,500
My Dad taught me to fulfill my
dreams with hard work and real efforts.

703
01:19:58,041 --> 01:20:01,083
But I have cheated to get what I wanted.

704
01:20:02,791 --> 01:20:05,500
That turned me into another person.

705
01:20:07,416 --> 01:20:10,291
I hurt my good friends

706
01:20:11,625 --> 01:20:13,833
and even the people I love the most.

707
01:20:15,250 --> 01:20:20,375
Then I realize the worst thing is
not about failing to achieve my dreams,

708
01:20:21,541 --> 01:20:24,208
but about losing myself.

709
01:20:25,458 --> 01:20:29,000
Thank you everyone for
giving me a chance to make it right.

710
01:20:31,416 --> 01:20:33,541
I'd like to withdraw from the contest.

711
01:20:35,958 --> 01:20:36,958
Why is that?

712
01:21:35,125 --> 01:21:37,583
<i>I still can't believe my eyes.</i>

713
01:21:38,083 --> 01:21:40,416
<i>Hundreds of yellow ribbons are flying.</i>

714
01:22:03,958 --> 01:22:06,375
<i>Let's end the movie with a wide shot!</i>

715
01:22:06,458 --> 01:22:09,666
See? I just quit in
the middle of the contest.

716
01:22:09,750 --> 01:22:13,625
Are you curious about what
I do after this to follow my dream?

717
01:22:14,125 --> 01:22:16,875
If you want to, ask
your friends to watch this movie

718
01:22:16,958 --> 01:22:20,458
so that the producer will have
enough budget for the next sequence.

719
01:22:20,541 --> 01:22:22,083
See you then!
